                  Brandon's primary research as part of Advanced Threat Research at Verisign involves identifying 
				  malicious attacks, conducting APT malicious code analysis, tool development and devising strategies 
				  to counter threats earlier in their decision cycle. Brandon maintains "PDF X-RAY" and a blog at 
				  blog.9bplus.com where he reports on targeted attacks, malicious file analysis and tool development. 
				  His research on various security topics has gained accolades from many major software vendors. 
                  For both attackers and researchers to be successful, they must change. As researchers, we observe 
				  this often and usually need to play catch-up to understand how the change impacts us. Recently, 
				  an XDP file was found exploiting an older vulnerability and dropping malware that fit targeted samples.
                  This talk will cover the discovery process of the XDP file, how it was reversed, recreated and then exposed 
				  to the public. Also, new files found at the end of June will be reviewed and explained. The talk will end 
				  with predictions and thoughts on this technique and a timeline of known samples.
				  
                  
